<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68b29c0-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10320"><num value="10320">§ 10320.</num><heading> Records of seamen</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall prescribe regulations requiring vessel owners to maintain records of seamen on matters of engagement, discharge, and service. A vessel owner shall make these records available to the seaman and the Coast Guard on request.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf68b29c1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/569">97 Stat. 569</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/206/tIV/s411">Pub. L. 103–206, title IV, § 411</ref>, <date date="1993-12-20">Dec. 20, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/2437">107 Stat. 2437</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
